		<h3>Imagine Bella Coronavirus Update Friday March 20th<br>
</h3>
		
		
		
		
		
		
		
			<span class="text rteSpan">Dear IBAE Families,<br><br>We continue to work to meet the needs of our students, staff, and families while keeping your health and safety a top priority. As directed by Governor Mike DeWine, our school continue to be closed through April 6.<br><br>Please note the following updates/changes:<br><br>During our spring break (March 23 through March 27) school and offices will be closed.<br><br>Cleaning/Disinfecting of school building:<br><br>We are currently cleaning and disinfecting target areas while building is under limited use. Building will also undergo thorough cleaning and disinfection. Once this occurs, the building will be closed and unoccupied leading up to the reopening of school. Please note: this information is subject to change based upon additional information received.<br><br>Internet access assistance for families:<br><br>Charter will offer free Spectrum broadband and Wi-Fi access for 60 days to households with K-12 and/or college students who do not already have a Spectrum broadband subscription and at any service level up to 100 Mbps. To enroll call 1-844-488-8395. <br>Spectrum Internet Assist- Get high-speed internet at an affordable price. Spectrum Internet Assist is available exclusively to qualified households.<br><br>We will continue to provide updates on this page as information is made available. <br><br>Thank you for your patience as we continue to navigate this health emergency.<br><br>Mr. Dutt</span><br><div align="right">
		<br clear="both"><br><span class="news-posted-on">
					Posted on March 20, 2020
					 
						• Updated on March 21, 2020
					
